1
00:00:14,360 --> 00:00:17,440
♪In the airport lounge
at the break of day♪

2
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:22,240
♪A page of dust beneath my fingers♪

3
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:25,160
♪Filled with stories♪

4
00:00:25,160 --> 00:00:28,280
♪That others never got to tell♪

5
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,960
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

6
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:35,600
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

7
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:37,160
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

8
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:40,040
♪The world is split an inch wider♪

9
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:42,600
♪Raise your eyes, face the light♪

10
00:00:42,760 --> 00:00:45,080
♪See the truth, and see the fright♪

11
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:46,800
♪Guard the crack within this door♪

12
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:52,600
♪Keep the way back home
always burning bright♪

13
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:57,040
♪The camera pans
across the boarding crowd♪

14
00:00:57,080 --> 00:00:59,200
♪Some wear a smile,
some have their eyes adrift♪

15
00:00:59,280 --> 00:01:01,440
♪A red suitcase♪

16
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:05,360
♪Tied with faded pasts
and broken prayers♪

17
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:09,400
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

18
00:01:09,480 --> 00:01:12,080
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

19
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:13,960
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

20
00:01:14,040 --> 00:01:17,400
♪It's the heartbeat
echoing the call of law♪

21
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:30,000
[Gimlet Eyes]

22
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:33,000
[Episode 17]

23
00:01:34,560 --> 00:01:36,280
If I'm not mistaken,

24
00:01:36,840 --> 00:01:37,840
this painting

25
00:01:37,920 --> 00:01:40,680
was also brokered to Chen Wei
through Long Shuo.

26
00:01:41,360 --> 00:01:42,360
I asked you before

27
00:01:42,600 --> 00:01:44,320
whether this painting was clean.

28
00:01:44,520 --> 00:01:45,520
Remember what you told me?

29
00:01:45,760 --> 00:01:47,040
Did you actually check it out?

30
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:48,920
If you had,

31
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:50,840
you would've traced it back
to Long Shuo.

32
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:53,000
Why would he do all this?

33
00:01:55,120 --> 00:01:57,360
He was Sa Ziyi's lover.

34
00:01:57,800 --> 00:01:59,760
Sa Ziyi's cause of death
is still unknown.

35
00:02:00,280 --> 00:02:02,240
You think he doesn't want to know
who killed her?

36
00:02:02,720 --> 00:02:04,560
Whoever took over Sa Ziyi's turf

37
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:06,160
is the prime suspect.

38
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:07,600
Who else would he come to but you?

39
00:02:08,520 --> 00:02:09,880
He couldn't find you himself.

40
00:02:10,240 --> 00:02:12,880
So he used the doll to get Customs
to find you for him.

41
00:02:13,440 --> 00:02:15,400
Now you get it, right?

42
00:02:17,080 --> 00:02:17,840
But

43
00:02:18,360 --> 00:02:20,480
Chen Wei doesn't even know who I am.

44
00:02:20,560 --> 00:02:21,800
He's never even seen my face.

45
00:02:22,320 --> 00:02:23,200
What about Ken?

46
00:02:24,360 --> 00:02:27,040
Ken was directly
involved in moving the painting.

47
00:02:27,560 --> 00:02:29,360
What if Long Shuo's already found him?

48
00:02:30,440 --> 00:02:31,400
Probably not.

49
00:02:32,080 --> 00:02:32,840
Du Li.

50
00:02:33,920 --> 00:02:35,320
Looks like life's been

51
00:02:35,320 --> 00:02:36,720
a little too easy for you lately.

52
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:40,120
You're starting to look
just like Sa Ziyi back then,

53
00:02:40,120 --> 00:02:41,360
spoiled and careless.

54
00:02:42,160 --> 00:02:43,120
Take my advice,

55
00:02:43,120 --> 00:02:44,320
don't follow in her footsteps.

56
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:46,760
Or death'll be staring you in the face
before you know it.

57
00:02:48,760 --> 00:02:49,800
Understood, Mr. E.

58
00:02:50,240 --> 00:02:52,640
I'll send someone to look into Ken.

59
00:02:52,720 --> 00:02:53,960
We'll dig deep.

60
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:58,680
So, should we stop
moving the painting for now?

61
00:02:59,040 --> 00:02:59,640
No.

62
00:03:00,360 --> 00:03:01,160
It has to go.

63
00:03:02,040 --> 00:03:02,960
Why?

64
00:03:03,520 --> 00:03:04,560
To protect ourselves.

65
00:03:06,200 --> 00:03:06,760
First,

66
00:03:07,160 --> 00:03:09,640
Chen Wei is already
Long Shuo's eyes and ears.

67
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:11,360
You still want to keep him around?

68
00:03:12,480 --> 00:03:13,120
Second,

69
00:03:14,240 --> 00:03:16,520
Lawyer Song failed to frame Guo Cong.

70
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:18,600
You think Customs
won't start digging into him?

71
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:20,600
Third,

72
00:03:21,320 --> 00:03:23,120
this painting is
a Yuan Dynasty artifact.

73
00:03:23,960 --> 00:03:25,440
You think anyone
dealing in something like that

74
00:03:25,440 --> 00:03:26,360
has clean hands?

75
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:27,920
Any one of these three

76
00:03:27,920 --> 00:03:30,280
could bring trouble to our door.

77
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:32,520
They're already expendable.

78
00:03:33,080 --> 00:03:34,480
Letting them move the painting

79
00:03:34,880 --> 00:03:36,880
is basically giving them a way out.

80
00:03:37,320 --> 00:03:40,120
If they make it out,
they can live it up overseas.

81
00:03:40,600 --> 00:03:41,760
If they don't…

82
00:03:42,640 --> 00:03:43,440
Du Li,

83
00:03:44,360 --> 00:03:46,240
then you'd better
start worrying about Ken.

84
00:03:48,200 --> 00:03:50,680
Mr. E, if you knew all this,

85
00:03:51,240 --> 00:03:53,880
why didn't you tell me sooner?

86
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,800
Because it was only a theory.

87
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:58,680
I needed the doll to confirm it.

88
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:00,240
How could I have told you before that?

89
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:03,320
But your theory cost me a lot.

90
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:05,720
You cut off an arm to save your life.
Understand?

91
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:09,120
Right now, we've only
lost a few fingers.

92
00:04:09,720 --> 00:04:11,120
If we keep dragging this out,

93
00:04:11,240 --> 00:04:12,800
we'll lose the whole arm.

94
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:14,880
If you make it through this,

95
00:04:15,360 --> 00:04:16,680
keep looking for Long Shuo.

96
00:04:17,280 --> 00:04:18,960
He's the real problem.

97
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:25,320
Useless.

98
00:04:30,720 --> 00:04:31,280
What now?

99
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:33,720
What do you think?

100
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:35,400
We keep going and hope for the best.

101
00:04:35,720 --> 00:04:36,520
Finish the job.

102
00:04:36,520 --> 00:04:37,360
But Li!

103
00:04:38,440 --> 00:04:40,320
What if they really get caught?

104
00:04:41,320 --> 00:04:42,800
Then that's their fate.

105
00:04:47,240 --> 00:04:47,600
Fine.

106
00:06:51,840 --> 00:06:52,200
Mr. Long.

107
00:06:53,320 --> 00:06:54,040
What's up?

108
00:06:54,840 --> 00:06:56,240
About the painting,

109
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:57,360
I reported it to the higher-ups.

110
00:06:57,640 --> 00:06:59,240
They put me in charge of this job.

111
00:06:59,480 --> 00:07:00,560
They're giving me this much.

112
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:02,760
Congratulations.

113
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:04,720
Looks like you're moving up.

114
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:05,320
Not really.

115
00:07:05,320 --> 00:07:07,160
It's all thanks to the chance
you gave me.

116
00:07:08,480 --> 00:07:09,520
So, Mr. Long,

117
00:07:09,520 --> 00:07:11,040
can I ask you something?

118
00:07:11,560 --> 00:07:13,360
What exactly are you trying

119
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:14,560
to find out from me?

120
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:19,480
Nothing major.

121
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:22,720
Just a personal score to settle

122
00:07:23,240 --> 00:07:24,440
with your boss.

123
00:07:25,640 --> 00:07:27,760
If we could sit down face to face,
it'd all blow over.

124
00:07:28,400 --> 00:07:29,800
But I can never get to him.

125
00:07:30,960 --> 00:07:32,720
So I had to go the long way around

126
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:34,000
and work my way up through you.

127
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:36,440
Mr. Long,

128
00:07:36,800 --> 00:07:38,200
if I handle this deal well,

129
00:07:38,520 --> 00:07:39,800
I figure

130
00:07:40,120 --> 00:07:41,320
I'll get a chance to meet the top brass.

131
00:07:41,440 --> 00:07:42,800
I'll pass your message to them.

132
00:07:43,960 --> 00:07:45,200
I appreciate that.

133
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:47,360
When are you planning

134
00:07:47,840 --> 00:07:48,920
to make the move?

135
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:52,040
Honestly, I don't know yet.

136
00:07:52,320 --> 00:07:54,280
Usually, the seller
gives us the flight number

137
00:07:54,280 --> 00:07:55,240
a day in advance,

138
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:56,280
and we head straight there.

139
00:07:58,240 --> 00:08:00,080
Being cautious is a good thing.

140
00:08:01,480 --> 00:08:03,120
Well, here's to a smooth run.

141
00:08:03,520 --> 00:08:04,720
Thanks, Mr. Long.

142
00:08:04,880 --> 00:08:06,440
I booked us a private room up ahead.

143
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:11,240
Uncle Xiang.

144
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:12,800
What are you messing with?

145
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:13,120
Here.

146
00:08:13,120 --> 00:08:13,480
Let me help.

147
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:15,000
Where does this go?

148
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:15,480
No.

149
00:08:15,480 --> 00:08:16,080
I put it here

150
00:08:16,080 --> 00:08:16,520
just now.

151
00:08:16,760 --> 00:08:17,520
Just moved it over.

152
00:08:18,520 --> 00:08:19,000
Set it down properly.

153
00:08:20,040 --> 00:08:21,000
Listen, don't move

154
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:21,920
my stuff around.

155
00:08:21,960 --> 00:08:23,760
Or I can never find anything again.

156
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:27,520
You've got more and more stuff
piled up in here.

157
00:08:29,440 --> 00:08:31,280
How long has it been
since you last came by?

158
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:34,120
When you were a kid,
you'd come straight here after school.

159
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:35,040
Couldn't get rid of you.

160
00:08:35,280 --> 00:08:36,080
And now what?

161
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:37,000
You're at Customs,

162
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:38,880
and you don't even
bother stopping by anymore?

163
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:41,200
Come on,

164
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:42,360
of course I want to.

165
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:44,200
The problem is, every time

166
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:45,200
I come here,

167
00:08:45,280 --> 00:08:46,120
I feel like pocketing something.

168
00:08:46,640 --> 00:08:47,800
But Customs has rules.

169
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:48,880
We can't do that.

170
00:08:48,880 --> 00:08:50,120
You know how painful that is?

171
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:51,800
So, out of sight, out of mind.

172
00:08:52,960 --> 00:08:54,280
That excuse sounds well-rehearsed.

173
00:08:54,760 --> 00:08:55,640
If you don't want to come, fine.

174
00:08:55,640 --> 00:08:56,880
Spare me the excuses.

175
00:08:57,280 --> 00:08:58,200
Let me tell you,

176
00:08:58,600 --> 00:09:00,560
half the stuff here
belonged to your father.

177
00:09:00,560 --> 00:09:02,640
That means half of it is yours.

178
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:04,840
Taking your own things is totally fine.

179
00:09:06,240 --> 00:09:07,680
Fine, I'll come by more often.

180
00:09:08,040 --> 00:09:09,240
Just don't blame me

181
00:09:09,240 --> 00:09:10,440
if I mess the place up.

182
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:11,280
Uncle Xiang,

183
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:14,480
what did you call me over for today?

184
00:09:15,160 --> 00:09:17,280
Why is a young guy like you
stuck at home all day?

185
00:09:17,280 --> 00:09:18,640
Go ask a girl out.

186
00:09:19,520 --> 00:09:20,040
Wait…

187
00:09:21,920 --> 00:09:23,880
Did my mom get in your ear too?

188
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:26,480
She nags me every day about

189
00:09:26,480 --> 00:09:27,680
finding a wife.

190
00:09:27,680 --> 00:09:29,120
I came here to get some peace.

191
00:09:29,280 --> 00:09:31,400
Your mom didn't have to get to me.

192
00:09:31,680 --> 00:09:34,280
We've been on the same side all along.

193
00:09:36,400 --> 00:09:37,400
Seriously.

194
00:09:37,640 --> 00:09:38,280
Tao!

195
00:09:39,480 --> 00:09:40,520
Tao!

196
00:09:40,520 --> 00:09:41,240
Tao? Come on…

197
00:09:41,920 --> 00:09:43,240
Guo Cong's here!

198
00:09:44,160 --> 00:09:45,200
Where is she?

199
00:09:46,920 --> 00:09:48,040
Coming right down!

200
00:09:51,040 --> 00:09:51,640
Hi there.

201
00:09:51,720 --> 00:09:52,240
Come on in.

202
00:09:53,840 --> 00:09:54,440
Uncle Xiang…

203
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:56,120
Look,

204
00:09:56,320 --> 00:09:58,160
your mom assigned me a mission.

205
00:09:58,160 --> 00:09:59,200
I tried to get out of it,

206
00:09:59,200 --> 00:09:59,880
but I couldn't.

207
00:10:02,160 --> 00:10:02,600
Uncle Xiang,

208
00:10:03,240 --> 00:10:04,520
she's not right for me.

209
00:10:04,880 --> 00:10:06,480
Anyway, spend more time together first.

210
00:10:06,960 --> 00:10:08,200
People have a lot of sides to them.

211
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:10,480
You need different settings,

212
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:12,680
different situations
to see different sides.

213
00:10:12,680 --> 00:10:14,000
Maybe you'll like one of them.

214
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:15,400
So I'm just here

215
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:16,640
to fulfill my mom's mission.

216
00:10:17,640 --> 00:10:18,640
Then at least buy me lunch.

217
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:21,160
When she gets here, smile.

218
00:10:21,160 --> 00:10:21,920
Don't make things awkward.

219
00:10:21,920 --> 00:10:22,680
But I…

220
00:10:23,920 --> 00:10:24,960
Guo Cong, you're here.

221
00:10:25,520 --> 00:10:26,000
I'm here.

222
00:10:26,880 --> 00:10:27,400
Tao, sit.

223
00:10:29,400 --> 00:10:30,600
You remember this?

224
00:10:31,480 --> 00:10:33,400
I was just chatting with Mr. Xiang,

225
00:10:33,400 --> 00:10:34,320
and he told me so many stories

226
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:36,200
about you playing here
when you were little.

227
00:10:36,760 --> 00:10:38,160
It sounds like a dream.

228
00:10:38,520 --> 00:10:39,840
You're too kind.

229
00:10:39,960 --> 00:10:41,600
This place is basically a junkyard.

230
00:10:41,840 --> 00:10:43,200
Only he cares about all this stuff.

231
00:10:43,880 --> 00:10:45,120
They may be old,

232
00:10:45,240 --> 00:10:46,520
but every piece here carries history.

233
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:48,040
That's true.

234
00:10:48,040 --> 00:10:50,040
My uncle's got all that history
in his head.

235
00:10:51,640 --> 00:10:52,160
Uncle Xiang,

236
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:53,160
why don't you

237
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:54,880
show Tao around

238
00:10:54,880 --> 00:10:55,720
and tell her all about it?

239
00:10:55,960 --> 00:10:57,000
I don't have time for that.

240
00:10:57,200 --> 00:10:58,440
I promised a regular customer

241
00:10:58,440 --> 00:11:00,840
I'd help find a matching pair
of old window lattices.

242
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:02,320
I asked you to come

243
00:11:02,960 --> 00:11:04,840
because I want you

244
00:11:04,880 --> 00:11:05,920
to teach Tao photography.

245
00:11:07,280 --> 00:11:08,880
I'm an amateur myself.

246
00:11:09,760 --> 00:11:10,160
That's fine.

247
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:12,160
Just teach her the basics.

248
00:11:12,560 --> 00:11:13,880
The camera and film

249
00:11:13,880 --> 00:11:15,000
are all ready to go.

250
00:11:15,080 --> 00:11:16,000
Go take some shots,

251
00:11:16,440 --> 00:11:17,960
and when you get back,
we'll have lunch together

252
00:11:17,960 --> 00:11:19,280
and develop the film.

253
00:11:20,440 --> 00:11:21,240
Well,

254
00:11:21,400 --> 00:11:22,960
thanks in advance, Mentor.

255
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:24,560
Don't call me that.

256
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:25,840
Customs has rules,

257
00:11:25,840 --> 00:11:27,000
no small cliques.

258
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:29,880
But Zhang Yu calls you that too.

259
00:11:30,080 --> 00:11:31,320
Zhang Yu's different.

260
00:11:34,040 --> 00:11:35,440
Alright, what are you waiting for?

261
00:11:35,440 --> 00:11:36,120
Get going,

262
00:11:36,160 --> 00:11:37,120
while there's still daylight.

263
00:11:37,480 --> 00:11:37,880
Go on.

264
00:11:37,880 --> 00:11:38,640
Go, go, go.

265
00:11:39,560 --> 00:11:40,120
Alright.

266
00:11:41,760 --> 00:11:43,080
Make sure you've got everything.

267
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:43,480
Got it.

268
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:44,280
We're heading out.

269
00:11:47,160 --> 00:11:48,080
Mr. Xiang, we're off!

270
00:11:49,400 --> 00:11:50,760
Cong, take good care of her.

271
00:11:51,440 --> 00:11:51,760
Got it.

272
00:11:51,760 --> 00:11:52,640
Thanks.

273
00:12:19,800 --> 00:12:20,680
Guo Cong,

274
00:12:21,080 --> 00:12:22,240
my feet are killing me.

275
00:12:22,360 --> 00:12:23,640
Can we sit down for a bit?

276
00:12:24,240 --> 00:12:24,600
Sure.

277
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:25,360
Let's sit here.

278
00:12:29,440 --> 00:12:30,800
Mr. Guo told me

279
00:12:30,800 --> 00:12:32,600
to call him in five minutes

280
00:12:32,600 --> 00:12:33,640
and say it's an emergency.

281
00:12:35,040 --> 00:12:36,760
If I'm guessing right,

282
00:12:36,960 --> 00:12:38,520
he's in the middle of a tough date.

283
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:41,120
A tough date?

284
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:57,800
I've been
flying to Australia a lot lately,

285
00:12:57,800 --> 00:12:59,120
and I saw this neck massager

286
00:12:59,120 --> 00:12:59,960
selling like crazy.

287
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:01,640
I want to get one for your mom.

288
00:13:02,400 --> 00:13:03,160
No need.

289
00:13:03,680 --> 00:13:04,920
Her neck is perfectly fine.

290
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:06,600
You just don't know it.

291
00:13:06,800 --> 00:13:08,480
When we watch TV together,

292
00:13:08,480 --> 00:13:09,920
she's always rubbing her neck.

293
00:13:10,880 --> 00:13:13,040
And your couch is way too hard,

294
00:13:13,040 --> 00:13:14,560
it's really not great for older people.

295
00:13:17,080 --> 00:13:17,880
Okay, fine.

296
00:13:18,320 --> 00:13:19,000
Go ahead and get one.

297
00:13:19,680 --> 00:13:20,480
Let me know how much it is,

298
00:13:20,480 --> 00:13:21,120
and I'll send you the money.

299
00:13:21,360 --> 00:13:23,520
Can you stop
making everything about money?

300
00:13:23,520 --> 00:13:25,040
I want to give it to her as a gift.

301
00:13:25,440 --> 00:13:26,240
Guo Cong,

302
00:13:26,640 --> 00:13:28,720
can you stop drawing such clear lines
between us?

303
00:13:29,040 --> 00:13:29,840
That's not it.

304
00:13:29,880 --> 00:13:31,440
Customs has rules,

305
00:13:31,440 --> 00:13:32,240
you know that.

306
00:13:33,360 --> 00:13:35,320
Customs rules

307
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:36,600
won't let you make friends?

308
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:37,800
Or fall in love?

309
00:13:40,360 --> 00:13:41,400
That's not what I mean.

310
00:13:47,080 --> 00:13:48,240
Who's calling?

311
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:49,720
Work.

312
00:13:50,760 --> 00:13:52,680
Hello? Zhang Yu. What's up?

313
00:13:54,880 --> 00:13:56,760
Something happened at Customs?
What is it?

314
00:13:59,600 --> 00:14:00,440
Okay.

315
00:14:01,160 --> 00:14:01,960
Be right there.

316
00:14:02,680 --> 00:14:03,600
See you soon. Bye.

317
00:14:05,720 --> 00:14:06,520
Sorry,

318
00:14:06,520 --> 00:14:07,400
I've got to get back.

319
00:14:07,400 --> 00:14:08,440
Something came up at Customs.

320
00:14:09,120 --> 00:14:10,400
How about this,

321
00:14:10,520 --> 00:14:11,560
if you still want to take pictures,

322
00:14:11,560 --> 00:14:12,880
go to the park up ahead.

323
00:14:12,880 --> 00:14:13,880
You can shoot there.

324
00:14:13,880 --> 00:14:14,920
And when you're tired,

325
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:16,800
go rest at my uncle's place, okay?

326
00:14:16,880 --> 00:14:18,000
Gotta go. Call me.

327
00:14:19,280 --> 00:14:20,800
Shouldn't I bring your camera back?

328
00:14:20,800 --> 00:14:21,440
Right.

329
00:14:21,440 --> 00:14:22,000
The camera.

330
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:22,840
Thanks.

331
00:14:23,080 --> 00:14:23,640
See you.

332
00:14:23,640 --> 00:14:24,800
Guo Cong.

333
00:14:25,960 --> 00:14:27,760
You're pretty good at reading people.

334
00:14:28,440 --> 00:14:29,680
But your acting

335
00:14:29,680 --> 00:14:30,840
is really terrible.

336
00:14:35,680 --> 00:14:37,360
Well… What acting?

337
00:14:38,080 --> 00:14:39,200
Just now,

338
00:14:39,760 --> 00:14:41,400
you were clearly texting someone.

339
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:43,440
You had Zhang Yu call to bail you out,
didn't you?

340
00:14:45,880 --> 00:14:47,640
At least you've got some conscience.

341
00:14:47,920 --> 00:14:49,280
You went out of your way to lie to me

342
00:14:49,760 --> 00:14:51,080
just so I wouldn't look like a fool.

343
00:15:01,040 --> 00:15:01,760
Actually,

344
00:15:02,760 --> 00:15:04,880
Tao, I wanted to tell you…

345
00:15:04,880 --> 00:15:05,680
Guo Cong,

346
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:07,800
we're not kids anymore.

347
00:15:08,560 --> 00:15:10,920
Whatever you have to say, just say it.

348
00:15:16,560 --> 00:15:17,440
I think

349
00:15:18,720 --> 00:15:20,280
you're a really kind person.

350
00:15:20,280 --> 00:15:22,520
I just don't think

351
00:15:23,480 --> 00:15:24,840
we're the right match.

352
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:26,640
Why do you say that?

353
00:15:29,200 --> 00:15:30,360
I've always felt that

354
00:15:30,360 --> 00:15:32,320
even though
we haven't known each other that long,

355
00:15:32,960 --> 00:15:34,760
you're a genuinely good person.

356
00:15:35,920 --> 00:15:38,120
If you think I'm a good person too,

357
00:15:38,240 --> 00:15:39,680
then why can't you give me,

358
00:15:40,200 --> 00:15:41,120
give us,

359
00:15:41,720 --> 00:15:42,920
a chance?

360
00:15:45,840 --> 00:15:47,080
When it comes to relationships,

361
00:15:47,360 --> 00:15:48,280
it's not as simple as

362
00:15:48,560 --> 00:15:50,400
you think I'm a good person,

363
00:15:50,400 --> 00:15:51,480
and I think you're a good person.

364
00:15:52,280 --> 00:15:53,720
It comes down to whether it feels right,

365
00:15:53,720 --> 00:15:54,360
right?

366
00:15:58,560 --> 00:15:59,280
So,

367
00:16:01,800 --> 00:16:03,120
you like her then?

368
00:16:04,160 --> 00:16:04,640
Who?

369
00:16:05,720 --> 00:16:06,440
Zhang Yu?

370
00:16:07,120 --> 00:16:08,320
She's my colleague.

371
00:16:12,680 --> 00:16:13,240
Okay.

372
00:16:14,760 --> 00:16:15,520
Good.

373
00:16:18,280 --> 00:16:18,880
Guo Cong.

374
00:16:21,680 --> 00:16:22,800
I like you.

375
00:16:25,080 --> 00:16:26,800
And I'll make you like me too.

376
00:16:29,480 --> 00:16:30,640
I'm willing to wait.

377
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:34,080
I believe

378
00:16:35,480 --> 00:16:37,440
feelings can grow.

379
00:16:53,800 --> 00:16:56,720
[Herbal Tea
Clears the Liver, Sharpens Vision]

380
00:16:56,720 --> 00:16:57,560
This is really bitter.

381
00:16:57,560 --> 00:16:58,520
[Herbal Tea
Clears the Liver, Sharpens Vision]

382
00:16:58,520 --> 00:16:59,680
But kinda addictive somehow.

383
00:17:00,400 --> 00:17:02,720
Do you think people are just like that?

384
00:17:02,720 --> 00:17:04,200
Always drawn to things
that make them suffer?

385
00:17:05,560 --> 00:17:06,680
Are you talking about yourself?

386
00:17:07,440 --> 00:17:08,320
Or someone else?

387
00:17:08,320 --> 00:17:10,400
Who else? Shen Taotao.

388
00:17:10,560 --> 00:17:11,320
Why'd she go after

389
00:17:11,320 --> 00:17:13,360
a hard nut like Mr. Guo?

390
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:16,000
Mr. Guo didn't say a word
about it on the phone.

391
00:17:17,440 --> 00:17:18,560
Think about it.

392
00:17:18,760 --> 00:17:21,320
Who else could make Mr. Guo

393
00:17:21,320 --> 00:17:22,840
call for help like that?

394
00:17:25,800 --> 00:17:28,640
I still don't think it was her.

395
00:17:28,640 --> 00:17:30,560
He's not that kind of person.

396
00:17:30,560 --> 00:17:31,720
If he wasn't into her,

397
00:17:31,720 --> 00:17:33,560
he wouldn't have gone off alone
with her.

398
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:35,320
Sure, he wouldn't.

399
00:17:35,640 --> 00:17:36,360
But what about his mom?

400
00:17:36,400 --> 00:17:37,320
And Mr. Xiang?

401
00:17:37,960 --> 00:17:38,840
Mr. Xiang?

402
00:17:40,480 --> 00:17:41,560
He wouldn't

403
00:17:42,240 --> 00:17:43,680
get involved in something like this,
would he?

404
00:17:45,080 --> 00:17:47,200
He cares so much about Mr. Guo.

405
00:17:47,320 --> 00:17:48,200
If you didn't know better,

406
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:49,680
you'd think he was Mr. Guo's father.

407
00:17:49,680 --> 00:17:51,320
Of course he'd get involved.

408
00:17:56,600 --> 00:17:57,960
Alright, enough guessing.

409
00:17:57,960 --> 00:17:59,280
Just call him and ask.

410
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:00,440
Again?

411
00:18:00,440 --> 00:18:01,360
Of course.

412
00:18:01,360 --> 00:18:02,480
What if he's still stuck there?

413
00:18:02,640 --> 00:18:03,800
Then your mission failed.

414
00:18:03,840 --> 00:18:04,400
Call him.

415
00:18:05,960 --> 00:18:06,920
Call him.

416
00:18:06,920 --> 00:18:07,680
Hurry up!

417
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:09,800
One call and you'll know.

418
00:18:12,960 --> 00:18:13,600
Speaker.

419
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:15,720
Speaker!

420
00:18:33,960 --> 00:18:34,920
Hello, Zhang Yu.

421
00:18:36,080 --> 00:18:37,960
So… did you manage to get out?

422
00:18:38,920 --> 00:18:39,720
Yeah, I'm out.

423
00:18:40,400 --> 00:18:41,720
Good. Glad you got out.

424
00:18:43,720 --> 00:18:46,280
Was that Shen Taotao just now?

425
00:18:46,440 --> 00:18:47,320
How did you know?

426
00:18:49,760 --> 00:18:51,200
Just guessing.

427
00:18:51,840 --> 00:18:53,240
Wait, Shen Taotao

428
00:18:53,240 --> 00:18:54,960
doesn't know I called you, right?

429
00:18:55,560 --> 00:18:56,680
She knows.

430
00:18:56,680 --> 00:18:57,520
I showed her.

431
00:18:57,760 --> 00:18:58,480
Otherwise,

432
00:18:58,480 --> 00:18:59,960
how would she believe
it was really a work call?

433
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:02,960
Mentor, you got me in trouble again.

434
00:19:03,040 --> 00:19:04,440
How did I get you in trouble?

435
00:19:05,760 --> 00:19:08,320
Last time,

436
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:11,280
you canceled that Australia trip,
remember?

437
00:19:11,320 --> 00:19:14,160
She thinks I got in the way
and made you cancel it.

438
00:19:14,320 --> 00:19:16,040
And now you're using me
as your cover again.

439
00:19:16,040 --> 00:19:17,520
She's definitely coming after me.

440
00:19:18,160 --> 00:19:20,200
You were the only person
I could think of, okay?

441
00:19:24,440 --> 00:19:24,960
But…

442
00:19:25,320 --> 00:19:25,640
Wait…

443
00:19:26,240 --> 00:19:26,840
Mentor…

444
00:19:26,840 --> 00:19:27,480
I…

445
00:19:27,480 --> 00:19:28,400
I mean,

446
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:30,640
if you're not into her,

447
00:19:30,640 --> 00:19:33,000
stop being alone with her all the time.

448
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:34,560
Or she's going to get the wrong idea.

449
00:19:34,760 --> 00:19:36,480
I wasn't planning to.

450
00:19:36,640 --> 00:19:38,240
Uncle Xiang tricked me into it.

451
00:19:38,400 --> 00:19:40,800
Mr. Xiang is involved in this?

452
00:19:41,680 --> 00:19:42,600
Back then,

453
00:19:42,600 --> 00:19:44,320
my mentor was always worried about this.

454
00:19:44,320 --> 00:19:46,360
He's looking out for me
for my mentor's sake.

455
00:19:46,360 --> 00:19:48,760
So that Australia trip

456
00:19:48,760 --> 00:19:50,320
with Shen Taotao

457
00:19:50,520 --> 00:19:52,480
was Mr. Xiang's idea too?

458
00:19:52,840 --> 00:19:54,880
I was planning to go to Australia
by myself.

459
00:19:55,280 --> 00:19:56,480
Uncle Xiang brought her to see me.

460
00:19:56,520 --> 00:19:57,640
She overheard us.

461
00:19:57,760 --> 00:19:59,360
So it was his idea after all.

462
00:19:59,760 --> 00:20:00,680
What? Didn't catch that.

463
00:20:01,360 --> 00:20:02,440
Nothing, never mind.

464
00:20:02,520 --> 00:20:04,160
Glad you're out. Talk later. Bye.

465
00:20:06,040 --> 00:20:09,120
You were the only person
I could think of!

466
00:20:09,120 --> 00:20:09,760
Stop it!

467
00:20:09,760 --> 00:20:11,200
You're in trouble, Yu.

468
00:20:11,240 --> 00:20:11,760
Nonsense!

469
00:20:12,040 --> 00:20:13,120
I was just thinking,

470
00:20:13,360 --> 00:20:15,000
don't you think

471
00:20:15,520 --> 00:20:16,840
Mr. Xiang's pushing

472
00:20:16,840 --> 00:20:17,920
Shen Taotao

473
00:20:18,080 --> 00:20:20,400
toward Mr. Guo a bit too hard?

474
00:20:20,520 --> 00:20:21,600
If not her,

475
00:20:22,080 --> 00:20:22,920
then how about you?

476
00:20:23,800 --> 00:20:26,520
How about you? Seriously!

477
00:20:47,280 --> 00:20:48,480
Tao, you're back?

478
00:20:48,760 --> 00:20:49,560
Where's Cong?

479
00:20:50,760 --> 00:20:52,280
He got a work call.

480
00:20:53,280 --> 00:20:54,320
Something came up. He left.

481
00:20:55,600 --> 00:20:56,520
That kid,

482
00:20:56,960 --> 00:20:58,160
he just left you there by yourself?

483
00:21:00,280 --> 00:21:01,720
This is on me.

484
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:04,280
I shouldn't have just

485
00:21:04,280 --> 00:21:05,880
sent you two off together like that.

486
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:06,720
This…

487
00:21:08,560 --> 00:21:09,240
Well…

488
00:21:10,680 --> 00:21:11,680
I…

489
00:21:11,800 --> 00:21:12,720
I know

490
00:21:12,760 --> 00:21:14,560
you really like Cong.

491
00:21:15,080 --> 00:21:16,320
But honestly, I never thought

492
00:21:16,320 --> 00:21:17,800
he'd just leave you there

493
00:21:17,800 --> 00:21:19,240
and run off by himself.

494
00:21:20,080 --> 00:21:21,840
So what are you thinking now?

495
00:21:24,560 --> 00:21:25,360
Honestly,

496
00:21:26,680 --> 00:21:28,920
getting rejected really hurts.

497
00:21:30,200 --> 00:21:31,080
But

498
00:21:32,040 --> 00:21:33,720
this is my own happiness
we're talking about.

499
00:21:34,240 --> 00:21:35,920
I want to try a little harder.

500
00:21:36,760 --> 00:21:37,720
Otherwise,

501
00:21:38,440 --> 00:21:39,840
I'm afraid I'll regret it later.

502
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:41,400
Good.

503
00:21:41,760 --> 00:21:43,240
That's what I like about you.

504
00:21:43,960 --> 00:21:46,280
But even though I've made up my mind,

505
00:21:47,040 --> 00:21:48,960
I don't know what to do next.

506
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:51,400
You know Guo Cong better than anyone.

507
00:21:51,960 --> 00:21:53,280
Can you give me some advice?

508
00:21:53,920 --> 00:21:55,760
Advice, huh?

509
00:21:56,760 --> 00:21:57,160
Okay.

510
00:21:57,560 --> 00:21:58,520
Here, hand me the camera.

511
00:21:59,920 --> 00:22:01,720
You poor thing, come here.

512
00:22:05,600 --> 00:22:05,960
Come on.

513
00:22:18,120 --> 00:22:18,720
Li,

514
00:22:19,120 --> 00:22:20,160
what brings you here?

515
00:22:20,240 --> 00:22:21,480
You could've called ahead.

516
00:22:21,840 --> 00:22:23,680
If I didn't come now,
Customs would beat me to it.

517
00:22:26,000 --> 00:22:26,920
What do you mean?

518
00:22:27,840 --> 00:22:29,360
Can that computer pull up
all the security footage

519
00:22:29,360 --> 00:22:30,240
from Yating's cameras?

520
00:22:30,840 --> 00:22:31,560
Yeah.

521
00:22:32,760 --> 00:22:33,880
Pull up the footage from the day

522
00:22:33,920 --> 00:22:35,200
you passed the message to Chen Wei.

523
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:37,000
The cameras facing the gallery.

524
00:22:57,280 --> 00:22:57,720
Stop.

525
00:22:58,280 --> 00:22:58,760
Zoom in.

526
00:23:01,440 --> 00:23:02,200
Who is that?

527
00:23:03,920 --> 00:23:04,680
Long Shuo.

528
00:23:06,120 --> 00:23:07,640
Customs doesn't answer to you.

529
00:23:08,680 --> 00:23:09,800
I've got things to do.

530
00:23:09,800 --> 00:23:11,160
Save the lecture.

531
00:23:12,200 --> 00:23:12,920
Stay where you are.

532
00:23:14,280 --> 00:23:15,600
I don't remember saying you could leave.

533
00:23:18,440 --> 00:23:19,720
That's Long Shuo?

534
00:23:21,560 --> 00:23:22,440
No question.

535
00:23:23,040 --> 00:23:24,640
I saw him once at Sa Ziyi's place.

536
00:23:25,040 --> 00:23:25,800
It's definitely him.

537
00:23:31,520 --> 00:23:33,120
How did he know where to find us?

538
00:23:34,280 --> 00:23:36,080
He's been working with Chen Wei
this whole time!

539
00:23:36,360 --> 00:23:37,920
You brought a wolf in
and didn't even know it!

540
00:23:41,760 --> 00:23:42,880
Can you make him disappear?

541
00:23:44,760 --> 00:23:46,680
Li, you scared me.

542
00:23:47,760 --> 00:23:49,760
I-I can't handle something like that.

543
00:23:53,320 --> 00:23:54,200
How about

544
00:23:56,040 --> 00:23:56,840
letting Dabao handle it?

545
00:23:57,960 --> 00:23:58,680
He's ruthless enough.

546
00:23:59,920 --> 00:24:00,920
I knew you didn't have the guts.

547
00:24:01,280 --> 00:24:01,880
Li.

548
00:24:04,360 --> 00:24:06,280
Long Shuo probably didn't see me.

549
00:24:06,520 --> 00:24:08,880
I came to pick up the message at night.

550
00:24:09,520 --> 00:24:10,440
Let's hope so.

551
00:24:11,600 --> 00:24:14,080
From now on,
stop everything you're doing.

552
00:24:14,440 --> 00:24:15,280
Don't go anywhere.

553
00:24:15,560 --> 00:24:16,600
Stay right here.

554
00:24:16,920 --> 00:24:17,720
Wait for my call.

555
00:24:18,520 --> 00:24:20,440
Right now,
all you can do is pray Chen Wei

556
00:24:20,480 --> 00:24:22,120
doesn't mess up the run.

557
00:24:28,120 --> 00:24:29,160
If he gets caught

558
00:24:29,440 --> 00:24:30,280
and gives you up,

559
00:24:31,800 --> 00:24:32,760
I can't protect you.

560
00:24:53,040 --> 00:24:54,120
Chen Wei.

561
00:25:00,760 --> 00:25:02,360
I sent you out to photograph people,

562
00:25:02,600 --> 00:25:04,360
and every single shot is of him.

563
00:25:05,880 --> 00:25:06,760
Tao,

564
00:25:07,880 --> 00:25:09,160
I honestly don't understand

565
00:25:09,160 --> 00:25:11,560
how you young people
deal with relationships these days.

566
00:25:12,040 --> 00:25:13,280
But one thing I do know

567
00:25:13,600 --> 00:25:14,760
is Cong doesn't understand it either.

568
00:25:15,640 --> 00:25:17,560
He's never even been in a relationship.

569
00:25:19,080 --> 00:25:20,720
He's been walking barefoot
his whole life.

570
00:25:20,720 --> 00:25:23,120
How would he know
what kind of shoes fit him?

571
00:25:28,920 --> 00:25:29,720
But here's the thing,

572
00:25:30,640 --> 00:25:32,400
that boy always has his guard up.

573
00:25:33,640 --> 00:25:35,840
He was only 15 when his father passed.

574
00:25:37,880 --> 00:25:39,800
It took me a lot of effort,

575
00:25:40,120 --> 00:25:41,960
nearly a whole year,

576
00:25:42,160 --> 00:25:44,480
before he finally called me uncle again.

577
00:25:45,960 --> 00:25:48,240
If you really want my advice,

578
00:25:48,760 --> 00:25:49,560
it's simple.

579
00:25:49,880 --> 00:25:50,640
Just one word.

580
00:25:51,080 --> 00:25:51,600
Persist.

581
00:25:54,360 --> 00:25:55,040
Persist?

582
00:25:55,160 --> 00:25:55,600
Exactly.

583
00:25:55,880 --> 00:25:58,040
Like water wearing down stone.

584
00:25:59,400 --> 00:26:01,240
Use all your time

585
00:26:01,240 --> 00:26:03,040
to slowly get closer to him,

586
00:26:03,760 --> 00:26:06,960
and all your energy

587
00:26:07,520 --> 00:26:09,200
into letting him see how good you are.

588
00:26:09,280 --> 00:26:11,480
Once he starts coming to you on his own,

589
00:26:11,800 --> 00:26:13,480
you won't be able to shake him off.

590
00:26:16,400 --> 00:26:17,400
I get it.

591
00:26:18,640 --> 00:26:20,080
Let me think about that.

592
00:26:21,080 --> 00:26:23,080
If you need me
to help behind the scenes,

593
00:26:23,160 --> 00:26:24,080
just say the word.

594
00:26:25,680 --> 00:26:26,480
Will do.

595
00:26:27,680 --> 00:26:28,680
Honestly,

596
00:26:28,680 --> 00:26:30,520
I've got my own selfish reasons too.

597
00:26:31,120 --> 00:26:32,640
I've always had a dream.

598
00:26:33,640 --> 00:26:34,400
I want to

599
00:26:34,440 --> 00:26:37,680
